Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.25,0:03:06.92,PlaceCard,,0,0,0,,{\pos(652,590)\fad(400,0)}Nagasaki Confucius Shrine · Historical Museum of China
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.29,0:03:10.13,PlaceCard,,0,0,0,,{\pos(632,590)\fs50\fad(400,0)}Ōura Church
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.50,0:03:13.13,PlaceCard,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\fad(410,0)\pos(613,620)}Glover Garden
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.72,0:02:58.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be3}As usual, Ran drew first prize in the shopping district's lottery,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.58,0:03:03.91,Thoughts,,0,0,15,,{\be6}so today, we've come to Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.88,0:03:14.37,Thoughts,,0,0,17,,{\be6}This is Glover Garden, where Thomas Blake Glover,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.37,0:03:20.16,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be3}an English{Scottish, but they say English} merchant who supported Shishi like Sakamoto Ryōma in the Bakumatsu period once lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.16,0:03:22.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be3}It's the most famous place in Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.91,0:03:26.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}What's she looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.65,0:03:29.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}The heart stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.48,0:03:30.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Heart stones?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.81,0:03:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Two of the paving stones in the Garden are shaped like hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.33,0:03:39.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}There's all sorts of legends about them,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.22,0:03:44.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}such as 'if a couple finds them they'll be married', and 'if you touch them your love will come true'.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.04,0:03:46.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.00,0:03:47.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}It's so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.04,0:03:49.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Now where's the other one?{I wonder where the other is? -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.27,0:03:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Never mind that, I want to try Nagasaki's famous {\i1}Champon{\i0} and {\i1}Sara{\i0} {\i1}Udon{\i0}—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.89,0:03:57.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.53,0:04:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}W-What was that just now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.17,0:04:02.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I'm sure they said 'Murderer!'...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.98,0:04:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.89,0:04:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Out the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.58,0:04:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Nobody move!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.67,0:04:14.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}You can leave the rest to the great detective Kogorō Mouri...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.07,0:04:17.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}What's with this victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.01,0:04:21.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}He came back to life!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.16,0:04:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Who exactly are yo—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.85,0:04:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.90,0:04:35.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}So I didn't make it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.24,0:04:37.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}We're sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.94,0:04:39.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Anyone'd get misled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.05,0:04:47.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}What was going on here was filming a 2-hour TV mystery drama based in the Nagasaki of the Bakumatsu period.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.35,0:04:51.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}A murder occurs in the Glover Residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.24,0:04:55.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}Sakamoto Ryōma, who was hiding in the Residence, takes on a detective role,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.26,0:04:58.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}aided by the young female doctor of Western Medicine, Ine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.34,0:05:04.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}He sets out to solve the case to clear the doubts people have of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.74,0:05:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}How about it, Ine?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.08,0:05:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Was a pistol used after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.12,0:05:12.17,CharCards,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\pos(646,544)}Kyōnosuke Sasahara (33)\NAs Sakamoto Ryōma
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.65,0:05:15.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}To think something like this would happen in our mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.88,0:05:18.67,CharCards,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\pos(640,544)}Benichiyo Yamashita (42)\NAs Tsuru
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.67,0:05:21.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}It's unfortunate for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.55,0:05:24.68,CharCards,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\pos(640,545)}Andrew Hatta (50)\NAs Glover
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.56,0:05:29.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}There's no mistake. He was killed by a pistol.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.43,0:05:32.69,CharCards,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\pos(641,544)}Futaba Nanao (23)\NAs Karasuma Ine
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.69,0:05:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Cut! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.09,0:05:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Hey, was that really okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.40,0:05:42.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}A temporary doctor shouldn't show that much emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.07,0:05:44.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}{\a6}It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.40,0:05:47.12,CharCards,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\pos(640,544)}Keisuke Sakakibara (45)\NTV Drama director
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.12,0:05:47.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}{\a6}Ine's a novice doctor, so it makes sense for her to be emotional.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.12,0:05:50.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}{\a6}O-Chiyo-{\i1}san{\i0}'s acting was great as always too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.41,0:05:50.45,CharCards,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\pos(640,544)}Akikazu Nakane (48)\NCameraman
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.45,0:05:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}{\a6}T-That's right, Benichiyo-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.70,0:05:53.75,CharCards,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)\pos(620,544)}Ryūhei Kishimura (30)\NAssistant Director
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.41,0:05:56.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Is that right? Then it'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.59,0:06:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Umm... next up is the scene where the victim's\Nmerchant friend, Soneya Chūbee, first appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.59,0:06:07.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Sazanami-{\i1}san{\i0}, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.19,0:06:08.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.35,0:06:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Treat me well, Bara-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.14,0:06:14.23,CharCards,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\pos(640,540)}Chōjirō Sazanami (45)\NAs Soneya Chūbee
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.23,0:06:17.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Sure. I'm counting on you, Chō-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.27,0:06:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Where are Soneya's props?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.44,0:06:19.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.73,0:06:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}{\a6}They're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.02,0:06:22.82,CharCards,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\pos(640,544)}Kazuomi Sakota (35)\NProp Master
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.42,0:06:29.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Isn't this a bit over-the-top?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.24,0:06:30.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.77,0:06:32.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Can't you do something about this comb too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.66,0:06:36.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}But... but those are from 'Madame Butterfly'...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.69,0:06:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}An opera lover as always, Sakota.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.80,0:06:42.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}But is this really okay, Bara-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.45,0:06:46.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Can we really start filming without even\Nknowing the end, or should I say, the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.51,0:06:52.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Well, even if it's a bit late, it'll be a masterpiece. This {\i1}is{\i0} Tatsumi we're talking about here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.39,0:06:57.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}She's quite a beauty, that girl playing the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.98,0:07:00.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Isn't that Futaba Nanao-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.53,0:07:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}She's a new actress thought to be getting her break soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.05,0:07:07.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Don't give me that! I can't just ignore it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.98,0:07:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Like I said, it'll be really bad, so make sure you cover it up...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.24,0:07:20.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I heard from Sonoko that Sasahara-{\i1}san{\i0}'s a handsome bachelor who's a regular among most-wanted boyfriend rankings.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.66,0:07:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I wonder what's happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.98,0:07:25.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\a6\be3\fs35}(Gesture referring to love in Japan)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.98,0:07:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Hmph. Maybe it's trouble related to {\i1}this{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.27,0:07:27.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.44,0:07:29.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}We're in trouble!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.89,0:07:32.76,CharCards,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)\pos(670,544)}Taizō Ōki (52)\NDrama Production Company Producer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.00,0:07:32.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}{\a6}T-T-Tatsumi's run off on us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.90,0:07:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Well, I knew he'd been stuck lately, but still...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.69,0:07:46.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Even though his old friends are all here for the first time in ages...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.74,0:07:48.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Wait a bit longer and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.60,0:07:50.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Argh! I'm at my limit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:53.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Your limit, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.05,0:07:54.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.46,0:07:56.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.94,0:07:57.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.49,0:08:00.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}What'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.90,0:08:03.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Sleeping Kogorō?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.93,0:08:04.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.10,0:08:07.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I beg you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.56,0:08:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Great detective Sleeping Kogorō, please deduce who the culprit is in this mystery drama!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.43,0:08:14.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.42,0:08:16.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.02,0:08:23.31,CharCards,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,544)\fad(250,250)}Kōsaku Tatsumi (45)\NScriptwriter
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.40,0:08:24.36,Thoughts,,10,10,0,,{\be6}{\a6}This mystery drama's scriptwriter, Kōsaku Tatsumi-{\i1}san{\i0}, is a veteran whose scripts have won various prizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.13,0:08:28.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}This drama isn't an adaptation, but an original work by Tatsumi-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.86,0:08:32.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}and the writing's taking too long, causing the filming to begin with an unfinished script.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.41,0:08:38.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}So the upcoming developments, not to mention the culprit of the case in the drama, are unknown to all but Tatsumi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.87,0:08:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}If this drama goes belly up, it'll wreck our company!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.80,0:08:51.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}If you can at least spot the culprit, Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}, I'll manage the rest somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.23,0:08:53.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}We're counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.50,0:09:01.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Just as I thought, it's impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.00,0:09:08.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}The script's not even half-finished, so no matter how much they ask, to spot a culprit from this is just too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.46,0:09:11.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}But you took the job anyway, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.29,0:09:14.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Saying there's no riddle that Sleeping Kogorō can't solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.78,0:09:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.45,0:09:19.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}True, there aren't enough clues...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.95,0:09:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.79,0:09:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}These are?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.67,0:09:28.92,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\c0\pos(196,38)}Serial Art Theft Case
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.92,0:09:30.17,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\c&H73787F&\fnSegoe\pos(700,381)}Illegally Sold\NAmong Fans
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.17,0:09:31.38,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\c&H3F4242&\pos(690,165)}{\fs30\fnHey Gorgeous M\fscx82\pos(687,110)}A Large-Scale Smuggling Organisation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.85,0:09:33.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}What're these?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.45,0:09:35.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Why are they here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.20,0:09:37.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}A group of art thieves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.14,0:09:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}That's it! So there was a real case it was based on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.60,0:09:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}You mean the culprit is the group of thieves?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.57,0:09:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}But they don't appear up in the current script at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.92,0:09:50.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}That's because it he hadn't put them in yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.91,0:09:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.82,0:09:56.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}If so, they wouldn't be hidden by being stuck up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.66,0:10:00.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Yes, right. I'm leaving now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.75,0:10:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}That's why you've gotta do something about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.94,0:10:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}How'd this happen...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.79,0:10:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ah, I'm worn out!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.26,0:10:16.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}In the end, we didn't find many clues at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.68,0:10:21.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I told you, the culprit's the group of thieves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.12,0:10:22.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Hey, Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.00,0:10:29.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ah, I'm Andrew Hatta, the actor playing Glover.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.83,0:10:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Doesn't my real face look just like\Nthe Glover statue in Glover Garden?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.07,0:10:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.46,0:10:45.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}Though when Glover was working with Ryōma, he was only 30 years old...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.70,0:10:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}{\i1}Detective Boy{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.82,0:10:53.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}You were thinking that the actor's much older than the real Glover was, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.24,0:10:54.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.13,0:11:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}The management are going through trouble at Ōki-{\i1}san{\i0}'s production company.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.60,0:11:04.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}That's why, thanks to Ōki-{\i1}san{\i0} and Sakakibara-{\i1}san{\i0}'s connections,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.56,0:11:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}most of the actors this time are\Nworking for lower pay than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.55,0:11:12.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Don't tell me that you are too, Andrew-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.34,0:11:15.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Yes. We go back a long way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.99,0:11:20.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}The director{-san} said that old friends had gathered for the first time in ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.23,0:11:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.43,0:11:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Sakakibara-{\i1}san{\i0}, Ōki-{\i1}san{\i0}, O-Chiyo-{\i1}san{\i0}, and Sazanami-{\i1}san{\i0} and I've worked together since the days before we became popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.32,0:11:33.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Tatsumi-san too, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.87,0:11:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.14,0:11:39.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}They hadn't cast anyone for the role of Glover but me,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.86,0:11:46.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}so they decided that we'd be a middle-aged couple, with me already married to Tsuru.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.14,0:11:49.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Maybe Tatsumi-{\i1}san{\i0} didn't agree with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.76,0:11:52.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}He was someone who liked to respect reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.11,0:11:56.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}So is that why he abandoned the script and vanished?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.63,0:11:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.78,0:12:03.49,PlaceCard,,0,0,0,,{\pos(620,617)\fad(350,0)\fscy95}Dutch Slope
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.83,0:12:07.25,PlaceCard,,0,0,0,,{\fad(350,0)\fscy95\fs50\pos(640,585)}Higashiyamate No.13
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.29,0:12:12.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Uncle Kogorō told me to ask you just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.14,0:12:15.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Well, I don't know. How about you, Bara-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.72,0:12:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Me neither. Finding bits of info was a secret hobby of Tatsumi's.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.81,0:12:28.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Hey, what're you doing?! It's only a matter of time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.55,0:12:43.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Hey, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.51,0:12:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}You're the kid who was with Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}, aren't you? {stopping here for today}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.93,0:12:58.81,PlaceCard,,0,0,0,,{\pos(641,588)\shad1\fad(350,0)}Nagasaki Museum of History and Culture
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.81,0:13:00.81,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\be1\pos(419,139)}{\pos(408,140)\c&HDBE1C1&}In 1582,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.81,0:13:00.81,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\be1\pos(540,139)\frz5.569}{\pos(408,140)\c&HDBE1C1&}the Tenshō embassy to Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.81,0:13:00.81,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\fax-0.4\be1\pos(987,97)\frz16.98\frx-20}{\pos(408,140)\c&HDBE1C1&}left Nagasaki
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.81,0:13:03.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Dad, Futaba-{\i1}san{\i0} says she was born in Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.75,0:13:08.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}And since my parts in the current script are all done filming,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.03,0:13:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I thought I could help you by being a guide...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.70,0:13:14.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Oh, that's a big help.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.85,0:13:17.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Visiting famous places with a beautiful actress tour guide!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.58,0:13:19.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}Running your mouth off again, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.16,0:13:23.46,PlaceCard,,0,0,0,,{\pos(641,592)\fad(350,0)}Site of Kameyama Shachū
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.95,0:13:23.95,Thoughts,,0,0,17,,{\be6}We visited the places related to the notes and photos
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.95,0:13:26.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}that Tatsumi-{\i1}san{\i0} made when creating this drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.96,0:13:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}This pistol's the one Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.96,0:13:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.26,0:13:36.55,PlaceCard,,0,0,0,,{\fad(350,350)\pos(640,588)}Kazagashira Park - Statue of Sakamoto Ryōma
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.60,0:13:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,15,,'The dawn of Japan is close!'
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.63,0:13:41.98,Dialogue,,0,0,15,,In Nagasaki, we call kites{tako} 'flags{hata}'.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.31,0:13:41.98,PlaceCard,,0,0,15,,{\fad(350,0)\pos(640,586)}Nagasaki 'Flag' Archive
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.27,0:13:45.81,PlaceCard,,0,0,15,,{\fad(460,460)\pos(640,586)}Spectacles Bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.10,0:13:44.73,Dialogue,,0,0,17,,{\be3}Ah, that's Spectacles Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.98,0:13:48.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}, gimme yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.46,0:13:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ah, how interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.49,0:13:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}, give them back!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.00,0:13:58.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Just a bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.28,0:13:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.62,0:14:02.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Man, I'm so hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.37,0:14:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.00,0:14:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}It can't be! It's Sleeping Kogorō!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.55,0:14:13.76,PlaceCard,,0,0,0,,{\fad(460,0)\pos(640,589)}Shikairō
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.01,0:14:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,15,,{\be6}This is the shop that invented {\i1}Champon{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.76,0:14:15.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I'm looking forward to eating it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.39,0:14:19.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Their {\i1}Sara{\i0} {\i1}Udon{\i0}'s pretty tasty, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.64,0:14:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}That thing's cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.70,0:14:24.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ah, this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.94,0:14:28.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I bought it at a shop by Glover Garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.75,0:14:34.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Oh, I've been waiting for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.54,0:14:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}It looks tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.32,0:14:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Delicious! It's the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.48,0:14:43.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}It's really tasty, right, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.06,0:14:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.61,0:14:49.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Aren't you going to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.49,0:15:00.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Well, actually, a few days ago, Tatsumi-{\i1}sensei{\i0} was almost hit by a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.13,0:15:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}What'd you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.50,0:15:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}He said that he thought someone pushed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.69,0:15:09.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.02,0:15:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Why didn't you mention it earlier?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.38,0:15:12.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.93,0:15:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Anyway, Tatsumi-{\i1}sensei{\i0} might've disappeared because he thought his life was in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.92,0:15:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}In the end, we didn't find any usable clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.30,0:15:37.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Tatsumi-{\i1}sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.00,0:15:37.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Futaba-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.68,0:15:45.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Is that Tatsumi-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.46,0:16:03.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}We lost him...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.33,0:16:09.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}Why was she running so desperately?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.60,0:16:19.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.37,0:16:20.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ah, Ōki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.90,0:16:26.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}What?! Tatsumi-{\i1}san{\i0} sent part two of the script in an e-mail?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.35,0:16:29.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}And is the culprit's name in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.06,0:16:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}What? It's still not finished?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.70,0:16:42.91,PlaceCard,,0,0,0,,{\fad(450,0)\fsp2\pos(640,587)}Dejima
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.16,0:16:47.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.49,0:16:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}A-Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.24,0:16:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}S-Somehow...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.55,0:17:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}It's strange, they were fixed in place...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.25,0:17:02.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Please, be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.26,0:17:06.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Even so, that was amazing, young lady. Was that karate?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.98,0:17:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Though she may not look it, she won the Kantō Tournament. She's the Champion!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.45,0:17:26.74,PlaceCard,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,593)\fad(460,460)}Trading Post Chief's House
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.73,0:17:25.42,Thoughts,,10,10,15,,{\be6}The second part of script that was e-mailed was also unfinished.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.42,0:17:29.02,Thoughts,,0,0,15,,{\be6}And in it, a second murder was depicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.62,0:17:32.32,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}The crime scene was the Dejima Trading Post Chief's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.32,0:17:35.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}The victim was a spy employed by the Nagasaki magistrate's office,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.88,0:17:40.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}and he left the kanji numeral nine as a dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.09,0:17:43.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}So what'd he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.48,0:17:49.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}For further information, ask the daughter of the Miura shipping agency, O-Tei.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.89,0:17:52.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Cut! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.16,0:17:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Though we've ended up with no holes in the schedule, the problem is what to do now...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.81,0:18:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Which means?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.49,0:18:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Without any foreshadowing, a new character's suddenly appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.11,0:18:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}The character has lots of puzzling lines, and I think it's an important role, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.35,0:18:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}We don't have any actor to play the character, nor time or money to bring someone from Tōkyō.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.62,0:18:16.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}That's a disaster!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.04,0:18:18.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Yes, a disast—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.40,0:18:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}You, how old are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.22,0:18:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I'm seventeen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.14,0:18:25.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}That's it! That's what we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.50,0:18:29.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.86,0:18:32.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}We're borrowing this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.77,0:18:36.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}You're kidding! I can't do this! It's too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.92,0:18:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I won't! I won't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.86,0:18:42.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Help me, Dad, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.45,0:18:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Go for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.87,0:18:45.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Go for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.11,0:18:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}No! It's the wrong way up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.39,0:18:49.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Amateurs are so useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.53,0:18:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}S-Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.78,0:18:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ah, that was my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.45,0:18:54.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Hey, will this really work?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.93,0:18:57.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}This isn't some school's art festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.21,0:18:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Don't worry. Relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.97,0:19:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}If you can at least say your lines, we'll take care of the rest somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.46,0:19:05.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ah, r-r-r-right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.63,0:19:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Then, try practising your lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.49,0:19:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}You can start off by looking at the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.74,0:19:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ah! Wait a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.65,0:19:15.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Okay, start!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.17,0:19:18.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}S-S-Sakamoto-{\i1}sama{\i0}, I-I am the daughter of the Miura family, O-Tei.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.47,0:19:22.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}W-What may I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.30,0:19:28.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Well, isn't that a 'dress', like a Western girl would wear?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.53,0:19:32.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}The daughter of the Miura family is famous throughout town for wearing exotic{lit. Spanish or Portuguese} clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.55,0:19:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}By the way, the man in the Trading Post Chief's House.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.30,0:19:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}He left behind the number nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.70,0:19:41.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Do you know anything about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.38,0:19:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Nine?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.31,0:19:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Numbers are important.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.38,0:19:49.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.20,0:19:48.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Numbers will solve everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.75,0:19:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ah, yes, Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.48,0:19:55.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}Why me too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.22,0:19:57.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Cut! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.48,0:20:02.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Take a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.23,0:20:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}What a weird line.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.66,0:20:08.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}'Numbers will solve everything.'
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.19,0:20:13.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}That reminds me, a lot of the actors in the production have numbers in their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.39,0:20:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Andrew {\c&H00FFFF&}Ha{\c}tta-{\i1}san{\i0} who plays Glover has one, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.39,0:20:17.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}{\fs30\be8\pos(368,644)}8
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.62,0:20:21.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6\pos(741,644)}{\fs30\be8\pos(705,640)}1000
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.62,0:20:21.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Playing his wife, Tsuru, is Beni{\c&H00FFFF&}chi{\c}yo Yamashita-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.58,0:20:26.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}{\be8\fs30\pos(856,648)}7
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.58,0:20:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Right. Futaba-{\i1}san{\i0}'s surname is {\c&H00FFFF&}Nana{\c}o too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.25,0:20:28.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}There's some in the staff too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.30,0:20:33.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}{\fs30\be8\pos(816,646)}3
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.30,0:20:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ōki-{\i1}san{\i0}'s name is Tai{\c&H00FFFF&}zō{\c}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.06,0:20:35.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}{\fs30\be8\pos(729,645)}1
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.06,0:20:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Sakota-{\i1}san{\i0}'s is {\c&H00FFFF&}Kazu{\c}omi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.35,0:20:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Sakamoto-{\i1}sama{\i0}, did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.31,0:20:45.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}There's a demon living here in Nakashima River.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.19,0:20:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.15,0:20:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}But you need not worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.11,0:20:54.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}The demon's weak point is the second tooth from the left in its lower jaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.07,0:20:56.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Cut! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.49,0:20:59.10,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}The demon's weak point...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.10,0:21:00.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}Yet another puzzling line.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.25,0:21:03.14,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.60,0:21:06.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}The font changes just for this line.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.29,0:21:07.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}Could this mean...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.64,0:21:18.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}Could these lines be a message from Tatsumi-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.10,0:21:24.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}And if O-Tei of the Miura family is a character created to convey that message...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.18,0:21:28.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}Then it must be about the reason for his disappearance!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.39,0:21:29.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}Then that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.86,0:21:30.86,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\be1\c0\pos(196,38)}Serial Art Theft Case
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.86,0:21:31.86,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\be2\c&H73787F&\fnSegoe\pos(700,381)}Illegally Sold\NAmong Fans
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.86,0:21:32.86,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\be2\c&H3F4242&\pos(690,160)}{\fs30\fnHey Gorgeous M\fscx82\pos(687,110)}A Large-Scale Smuggling Organisation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.37,0:21:42.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}That is all that I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.49,0:21:46.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Now, next I'll guide you to the first ever Western-style restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.72,0:21:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I've had enough! Let me out of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.00,0:22:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}He was probably punched. And with bare hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.73,0:22:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Hold on! Sakota!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.69,0:22:08.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Where's the ambulance?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.06,0:22:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I've called it! It'll be here soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.07,0:22:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Damn it! Who got you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.31,0:22:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Huh? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.10,0:22:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.33,0:22:25.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.18,0:22:27.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}I-It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.29,0:22:29.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}The karate champion?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.13,0:22:32.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}It can't be... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.01,0:22:36.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}H-Hey, Sakota! Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.43,0:22:37.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Sakota!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.92,0:24:02.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Where are you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.52,0:24:05.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}I'm just about to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.07,0:24:08.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}At the viewing platform... I was suddenly attacked by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.36,0:24:10.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}That's it! I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.05,0:24:12.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be6}The meaning of the dying message is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.41,0:24:15.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}The person who attacked Sakota-{\i1}san{\i0} and Sazanami-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.65,0:24:19.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}it was you, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.41,0:24:25.42,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,{\be3}On the next Conan: 'The Nagasaki Mystery Theatre (Present Day Case)'!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.42,0:24:30.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}Next Conan's Hint: Kanji Stroke Order!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.42,0:25:00.22,PlaceCard,,0,0,0,,{\fs28\bord0.7\a1\pos(876,621)}Look forward to the next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.42,0:24:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}{\a1}Dad, when did I—?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.20,0:24:33.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}{\a1}Sleeping Ran, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.34,0:24:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3}{\a1}I'll save you for sure.
